1. Open the `package.json` file and add the `devextreme` and `devextreme-angular` packages to the `dependencies` section:

        <!-- tab: package.json -->
        "dependencies": {
          ...
          "devextreme": "minor_21_2_package",
          "devextreme-angular": "minor_21_2_package",
        }
        
  Save the changes and install the dependent packages as follows:
    
    * In Visual Studio, build the application.
    * In [Angular CLI](https://github.com/angular/angular-cli), call the following command: `npm i`.

1. Add global style references to the Diagram and a [predefined theme stylesheet](/concepts/60%20Themes%20and%20Styles/05%20Predefined%20Themes/00%20Predefined%20Themes.md '/Documentation/Guide/Themes_and_Styles/Predefined_Themes/') (`dx.light.css` in the code below) to the `angular.json` file:

        <!-- tab: angular.json -->
        "styles": [
          ...
          "node_modules/devexpress-diagram/dist/dx-diagram.min.css",
          "node_modules/devextreme/dist/css/dx.light.css"
        ]

1. Open the `app.module.ts` file and import the Diagram component module:

        <!-- tab: app.module.ts -->
        // Imports the Diagram component
        import { DxDiagramModule } from 'devextreme-angular'; 

        @NgModule({ 
            // ... 
            imports: [
                // ...
                DxDiagramModule
            ] 
        })

1. Open the `app.component.html` file and add the following code. This code creates the DevExtreme Diagram UI component:

        <!-- tab: app.component.html -->
        <dx-diagram></dx-diagram>

Run the application.